 archival records to explore the root causes of this bold migration and its role in creating a region that continues to be a hotbed of social and environmental experimentation. Welcome to Resisterville is both an important look at an untold chapter in Canadian history and a compelling story of enduring idealism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAmericans -- British Columbia -- Kootenay Region -- History -- 20th century. 0aAmericanszBritish ColumbiazKootenay RegionxHistoryy20th century. 0aCounterculturezBritish ColumbiazKootenay RegionxHistoryy20th century. 0aCounterculturezBritish Columbia. 0aDissenters -- British Columbia -- Kootenay Region -- History -- 20th century. 0aDissenterszBritish ColumbiazKootenay RegionxHistoryy20th century. 0aDissenterszBritish Columbia. 0aImmigrantszBritish ColumbiazKootenay RegionxHistoryy20th century. 0aImmigrantszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975xDraft resisterszBritish ColumbiazKootenay RegionxHistoryy20th century. 0aVietnam War, 1961-1975xDraft resisterszBritish Columbia. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Peace.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311141999240uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482735540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774827355423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774827355/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-127709-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-141999-2  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyte